cution matches the source tip exactly. The reference format difference is minor — the knowledge file preserves the reference even if the label syntax isn't identical.\n\nLooking at the source structure now, there are two h2 sections: one for Batchletステップの場合 and another section that appears to be cut off. The hints for s2 cover the key classes and concepts like ItemReader, ItemProcessor, and ItemWriter, plus the Japanese terminology and validation-related terms. I'm double-checking the no_knowledge_content flag—it's set to false, so I can skip that validation. Everything looks consistent so far, though I want to verify that the batchlet status footnote reference in s1 is properly handled since it points to the JSR352 specification details. for ItemReader, ItemProcessor, and ItemWriter. So the knowledge file correctly includes these JSR352 references where they belong. I'm checking whether the ItemWriter reference I found is accurate to the source, and it appears to be — the knowledge file properly attributes the JSR352 specification details to these three interfaces while treating Batchlet differently since it's not explicitly framed as a JSR352 interface in the source material.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13763,"cache_read_input_tokens":18400,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":13763,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3aba6cbd-d935-458a-a909-a2cd15b9f4b5","uuid":"4d47d3be-3c9a-40af-8f43-23dc6cd96c80"}
